ex.php?title=Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia&amp;action=edit"/>\n<link rel="edit" title="Edit this page" href="/w/index.php?title=Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia&amp;action=edit"/>\n<link rel="apple-touch-icon" href="/static/apple-touch/wikipedia.png"/>\n<link rel="shortcut icon" href="/static/favicon/wikipedia.ico"/>\n<link rel="search" type="application/opensearchdescription+xml" href="/w/opensearch_desc.php" title="Wikipedia (en)"/>\n<link rel="EditURI" type="application/rsd+xml" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd"/>\n<link rel="license" href="//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/"/>\n<link rel="canonical" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//login.wikimedia.org"/>\n<link rel="dns-prefetch" href="//meta.wikimedia.org" />\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src="/resources/lib/html5shiv/html5shiv.min.js"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class="mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia rootpage-Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia skin-vector action-view">\t\t<div id="mw-page-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="mw-head-base" class="noprint"></div>\n\t\t<div id="content" class="mw-body" role="main">\n\t\t\t<a id="top"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteNotice" class="mw-body-content"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="mw-indicators mw-body-content">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en">Racial bias on Wikipedia</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="bodyContent" class="mw-body-content">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="siteSub" class="noprint">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="contentSub"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href="#mw-head">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href="#p-search">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="mw-parser-output"><table class="plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-content ambox-globalize" role="presentation">\n<tr>\n<td class="mbox-image">\n<div style="width:52px"><img alt="Globe icon." src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/48px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png" width="48" height="40" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/73px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Ambox_globe_content.svg/97px-Ambox_globe_content.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="350" data-file-height="290" /></div>\n</td>\n<td class="mbox-text"><span class="mbox-text-span">The examples and perspective in this article <b>deal primarily with U.S. and do not represent a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Countering_systemic_bias" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Countering systemic bias">worldwide view</a> of the subject</b>. <span class="hide-when-compact">You may <a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia&amp;action=edit">improve this article</a>, discuss the issue on the <a href="/wiki/Talk:Racial_bias_on_Wikipedia" title="Talk:Racial bias on Wikipedia">talk page</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Article_wizard" title="Wikipedia:Article wizard">create a new article</a>, as appropriate.</span> <small><i>(May 2015)</i></small> <small class="hide-when-compact"><i>(<a href="/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal" title="Help:Maintenance template removal">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></span></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG/220px-Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG" width="220" height="147" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG/330px-Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG/440px-Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG 2x" data-file-width="5184" data-file-height="3456" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Howard_University_edit-a-thon_B.JPG" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\n<a href="/wiki/Edit-a-thon" title="Edit-a-thon">Edit-a-thon</a> for <a href="/wiki/Black_History_Month" title="Black History Month">Black History Month</a> at <a href="/wiki/Howard_University" title="Howard University">Howard University</a>, a historically-black university</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class="thumb tright">\n<div class="thumbinner" style="width:222px;"><a href="/wiki/File:BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg/220px-BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg" width="220" height="220" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg/330px-BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/1d/BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg/440px-BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg 2x" data-file-width="693" data-file-height="693" /></a>\n<div class="thumbcaption">\n<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:BLT_NewOrleans_00.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"></a></div>\nEdit-a-thon for Visual Artists of the African Diaspora at the Joan Mitchell Center, hosted by <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Meetup/Black_Lunch_Table" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:Meetup/Black Lunch Table">Black Lunch Table</a> in New Orleans</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>There is a systemic <b>racial bias on Wikipedia</b> due to an under-representation of <a href="/wiki/People_of_color" class="mw-redirect" title="People of color">people of color</a> within its editor base.<sup id="cite_ref-philly_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-philly-1">[1]</a></sup> The past president of <a href="/wiki/List_of_Wikimedia_chapters" title="List of Wikimedia chapters">Wikimedia D.C.</a>, James Hare, noted that "a lot of <a href="/wiki/African-American_history" title="African-American history">black history</a> is left out" of Wikipedia, due to articles predominately being written by white editors.<sup id="cite_ref-NYtimes_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-NYtimes-2">[2]</a></sup> Articles that do exist on African topics are, according to some critics, largely edited by editors from Europe and North America and thus reflect their knowledge and consumption of media, which "tend to perpetuate a negative image" of Africa.<sup id="cite_ref-BusinessDay_3-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-BusinessDay-3">[3]</a></sup> Maira Liriano of the <a href="/wiki/Schomburg_Center_for_Research_in_Black_Culture" title="Schomburg Center for Research in Black Culture">Schomburg Center for Research in Black Culture</a>, has argued that the lack of information regarding <a href="/wiki/African_diaspora" title="African diaspora">black history</a> on Wikipedia "makes it seem like it\'s not important."<sup id="cite_ref-Fast_Company_4-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Fast_Company-4">[4]</a></sup></p>\n<table class="vertical-navbox nowraplinks" style="float:right;clear:right;width:22.0em;margin:0 0 1.0em 1.0em;background:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;padding:0.2em;border-spacing:0.4em 0;text-align:center;line-height:1.4em;font-size:88%">\n<tr>\n<td style="padding-top:0.4em;line-height:1.2em">Part of <a href="/wiki/Category:Discrimination" title="Category:Discrimination">a series</a> on</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th style="padding:0.2em 0.4em 0.2em;padding-top:0;font-size:145%;line-height:1.2em"><a href="/wiki/Discrimination" title="Discrimination">Discrimination</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0 0.1em 0.4em;padding-left:0; padding-right:0;">\n<div class="NavFrame collapsed" style="border:none;padding:0">\n<div class="NavHead" style="font-size:105%;background